## 3. CALL EMERGENCY SERVICES IF YOU EXPERIENCE:

**MEDICAL EMERGENCIES:**
- Chest pain, pressure, or tightness
- Severe difficulty breathing
- Crushing sensation in chest
- Pain radiating to arm, jaw, or back
- Severe dizziness or fainting
- Loss of consciousness
- Seizures
- Stroke symptoms (facial drooping, arm weakness, speech difficulty)
- Irregular or rapid heartbeat that doesn't resolve
- Bluish skin color
- Severe headache unlike any you've had before
- Any symptoms that feel life-threatening

**MENTAL HEALTH EMERGENCIES:**
- Thoughts of suicide or self-harm
- Plans or intent to harm yourself
- Thoughts of harming others
- Severe depression or hopelessness
- Psychotic symptoms (hallucinations, delusions)
- Severe panic that doesn't respond to usual techniques
- Inability to care for yourself
- Any psychiatric crisis

**DO NOT WAIT. DO NOT USE THE APP INSTEAD OF CALLING EMERGENCY SERVICES.**

